node.text: The ankles are very often overlooked when trying to improve squatting mechanics. Give this a try! Any dull stainless steel tool can work (back of a knife or similar) but @sidekicktool takes it to another level!!

node.text:
Protein icecream FTW

150g frozen banana
150ml almond milk (unsweetened)
25g @foodspring_athletics 3K chocolate protein
Sweetener to taste (vanilla)
Optional - peanut butter / peanut butter powder. 

Mix all ingredients and put in freezer - stir frequently to avoid crystallization. 

My favorite snack!

node.text:
What to eat when traveling?? Well, it doesn’t have to be complicated thanks to @rpstrength. 

Even more so now than ever you’ll have to PLAN AHEAD. 

1kg of chicken, 
500g rice and a 
HUUUGE mixed salad is going to keep me and @frederikaegidius fueled for the trip to MADISON AND THE CROSSFIT GAMES!

If you don’t have the option of cooking a lot before heading out here are my go to options for travel foods:

Boiled eggs, not the best for the person sitting next to you but it will clear TSA. 

Fresh fruits, full of good carbs and nutrients - make sure to finish them before leaving the plane if flying overseas :)

Nuts: every airport will have plenty of high fat snacks, but a bag of nuts is always a good choice if you can stick to just that one serving. 

Shy away from the quick fix sandwiches and other high processed foods - your stomach will thank you and you’ll arrive feeling better.
#travel #nutrition #protip #protein #carbs #fats #macros #food

Yes it’s definitely Games training 

This is the 4th year in Games training we do these intervals and yes they ALWAYS hurt 🔥 

5x2min on 2min off 
rest for 6min 
repeat for another 5 sets 👊

10m run 
7 wall ball
7 CTB Pull ups 
7 Power clean 135/95
7 STOH 135/95
7 burpee box jump over
7 Dumbbell snatch

node.text:
Freyja. Is. READY!!

I know this is a long shot and most likely won’t do anything but I have now tried everything else and I have to say I tried ALL I could. 

Like some of you might know USA is closed for travelers unless you have a visa.  I’m so Grateful that CrossFit got athletes approval +1 coach.  I’ll be allowed to take Freyja with me as well but will not have anyone to help me take care of her while I compete.  I know some of you think this is nothing but it feels incredibly difficult  even just thinking about not having Freyja with me for 2 weeks.  If for some reason you have a contact or a plug at DHS to help me get one more person in I have to at least try…. 🙏

Love to all of you ❤️

node.text:
Absolutely happiest of birthdays to this incredible person that I have chosen to spend my life with ♥️ the last 10 years have gone by soooo fast

Thank you for always being there no matter what and for all we have gotten to experience together - I couldn’t be more excited for everything that’s to come 

There’s no one else I would rather have by my side ♥️ 

Me and Freyja are so lucky 🥰

@frederikaegidius

node.text:
The pig will make an appearance @crossfitgames 2021 😏

Sled pull, pig flip, MU, pig flip, sled pull…. It’s gonna be a 💪 pump that’s for sure 😅🔥

#games #crossfit #pigflip #rogue @roguefitness

These numbers might not be BIG but it’s HUGE for me 

I’ve spent the last 11 months trying to recover and get stronger and fitter while balancing life with Freyja ❤️

I’ve put in a lot of hard work and had to stay patient while believing in the process taking it one step at a time

Now we are closing in on the @crossfitgames 

I’ll do everything I can to make her and myself proud at the Games this year

Snatch weight 87,5kg
Clean and Jerk 100kg 

#enjoylife #grateful #gamestraining #crossfit #oly @thetrainingplan

node.text:
THIS IS THE WAY

To be brutally honest, I’m making this post for myself and not for anyone else.

Read it through if you want, but I need myself to hear this..

Some days are hard. Some days, it seems everything is moving away from you, one thing in top of another piles up as obstacles in front of you - obstacles so tall you can’t seem to look over them and so wide you can’t peep past. 

These days I think about MY TEAM. The reason I wake up in the morning, the reason I work hard every single day. As long as MY TEAM is intact, healthy and happy everything else will be OK. Maybe not by the end of the day, maybe not tomorrow, but it will. 

Annie, this is the way. 

#dottir #motivation #real #struggle #brightside #family #team #love #lucky
